> <OLD>
>
> The tiny rodent continues on his way. He keeps quiet and uses his nose and
ears to direct him toward the source of the fire blasts. He hoped he could
at least see if Cheetor was anywhere close by. But like everything else, it
would be a shot in the dark.

<NEW>

As Rat Trap moved forward, using his small size and stealth he could easily
discern the obvious signatures of both Minion as well as the insectile
creatures that they had faced before.

As he came though the last of the brush he could finally make out the scene!

All around were more bodies of offline insectile creatures as well as
Insecticons, but in the air a battle was raging! There were many duplicates
of the deluxe Insecticons of Chop Shop, Ransack, Barrage and even Venom was
flying through the air - all of them having a definite minion energy
signature. At the same time the insectile creatures were also present in
large numbers, attacking these insecticon clones, it looked as if a storm of
mechanized insects were fighting back and forth.

In the center of all of this two large figures were battling, one looking
like a large heavily armored wasp/mantid cross breed and the other looking
like a powerful two headed dragon. Both of them moved around each other
warily as they looked each other over. The dual headed dragon of course had
the minion signature, while the other had the other was insectile.

As Rat Trap was taking all of this in several Insecticons landed on the
ground beside him bursting the over hanging brush, one was a Ransack clone,
the other a barrage. However what was immediately obvious was that they were
both offline, more victims of the battle above.

At the moment there was no sign of Cheetor, but the battle is large enough
that they could be in another section, or possibly not even here at all.

(TAG)

Preston

--bcaec51ba4113eebbb04a3007359
